 <jms-indent:block
xmlns:jms-indent="jonmsterling:indenting">
  
 <jms-indent:row>
   <fr:tex>\mathsf {intref}\colon  \mathbf {type}</fr:tex>
  </jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row>
   <fr:tex>\mathsf {new}\colon  \mathsf {Integer} \to  \mathsf {T}\,\mathsf {intref}</fr:tex>
  </jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row>
   <fr:tex>\mathsf {get}\colon  \mathsf {intref}\to \mathsf {T}\,\mathsf {Integer}</fr:tex>
  </jms-indent:row>

  
 <jms-indent:row>
   <fr:tex>\mathsf {set}\colon  \mathsf {intref} \times \mathsf {Integer}\to  \mathsf {T}\,{\mathopen {}\left (\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>
  </jms-indent:row>

 </jms-indent:block>
<fr:p>Models of very extensional equational theory including “garbage collection” found by Plotkin, Power; Staton. Adapted to “full ground store” (storage of pointers) by Kammar, Levy, Moss, and Staton.</fr:p><fr:p>Extensionality of models lost when moving to <fr:em>higher-order</fr:em> storage.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
