type="local"
addr="larsbirkedal">Lars Birkedal</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00OI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p><fr:link
href="palombi-sterling-2023.xml"
type="local"
addr="palombi-sterling-2023">Palombi and S. (2023)</fr:link> have contributed a modular method for building models of (non-univalent) guarded dependent type theory over an arbitrary base topos. As applied by <fr:link
href="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022">SGB’22</fr:link>:</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Any realisability topos <fr:tex>\mathcal {E}</fr:tex> contains an impredicative universe <fr:tex>\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Pick any <fr:em>internal</fr:em> well-founded order <fr:tex>\mathbb {O}\in \mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}</fr:tex>.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Then the <fr:em>relative</fr:em> presheaf topos <fr:tex>\mathcal {F} :\equiv  {\mathopen {}\left  [\mathbb {O}^{\mathsf {op}},\mathcal {E}\right  ]\mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is a model of guarded recursion and contains an impredicative universe <fr:tex>\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {F}}</fr:tex> defined from <fr:tex>\mathbb {M}_{\mathcal {E}}</fr:tex> by <fr:link
href="hofmann-streicher-1997.xml"
type="local"
addr="hofmann-streicher-1997">Hofmann—Streicher lifting</fr:link>.</fr:li></fr:ol></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
