root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2028</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#472</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-472.xml</fr:route><fr:title>Towards models of <fr:strong>iGHoTT</fr:strong></fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>10</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="danielgratzer.xml"
type="local"
addr="danielgratzer">Daniel Gratzer</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="larsbirkedal.xml"
type="local"
addr="larsbirkedal">Lars Birkedal</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00OI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We have not gotten around to adapting the <fr:link
href="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022.xml"
type="local"
addr="sterling-gratzer-birkedal-2022">SGB’22</fr:link> model of <fr:strong>iGDTT</fr:strong> to obtain a model of <fr:strong>iGHoTT</fr:strong>, which is much more complicated.</fr:p><fr:ol><fr:li>Let <fr:tex>\mathbb {A}</fr:tex> be a partial combinatory algebra.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Let <fr:tex>\square </fr:tex> be a suitable <fr:em>internal cube category</fr:em> in <fr:tex>\mathbf {PER}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {A}\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex>\mathbb {O}</fr:tex> be an internal well-founded order in the same.</fr:li>
  <fr:li>Then the category of internal presheaves of assemblies <fr:tex>{\mathopen {}\left  [{\mathopen {}\left (\square \times \mathbb {O}\right )\mathclose {}}^{\mathsf {op}},\mathbf {Asm}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {A}\right )\mathclose {}}\right  ]\mathclose {}}</fr:tex> is expected to form a model of <fr:strong>iGHoTT</fr:strong>{}.</fr:li></fr:ol><fr:p>Impredicative <fr:strong>HoTT</fr:strong> via cubical assemblies due to <fr:link
href="awodey-frey-speight-2018.xml"
type="local"
addr="awodey-frey-speight-2018">Awodey et al.</fr:link> and studied by <fr:link
href="uemura-2019-types.xml"
type="local"
addr="uemura-2019-types">Uemura</fr:link>, <fr:link
href="swan-uemura-2022.xml"
type="local"
addr="swan-uemura-2022">Swan</fr:link>.</fr:p><fr:p>Guarded <fr:strong>HoTT</fr:strong> via <fr:tex>\square \times \mathbb {O}</fr:tex> due to <fr:link
href="bbcgsv-2019.xml"
type="local"
addr="bbcgsv-2019">Birkedal et al. (2019)</fr:link>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"
toc="true"
numbered="true"
show-heading="true"
show-metadata="false"
expanded="true"
root="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2032</fr:anchor><fr:taxon>Slide</fr:taxon><fr:addr>#473</fr:addr><fr:route>unstable-473.xml</fr:route><fr:title>A more canonical model of <fr:strong>iGHoTT</fr:strong>?</fr:title><fr:date><fr:year>2024</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>10</fr:day></fr:date><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link
href="jonmsterling.xml"
type="local"
addr="jonmsterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="danielgratzer.xml"
type="local"
addr="danielgratzer">Daniel Gratzer</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link
href="larsbirkedal.xml"
type="local"
addr="larsbirkedal">Lars Birkedal</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00OI</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Even if internal presheaves of assemblies on <fr:tex>\square \times \mathbb {O}</fr:tex> works, the resulting model will be uncanonical from the <fr:tex>{\mathopen {}\left (\infty ,1\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>-categorical standpoint.</fr:p><fr:p>For example, if <fr:tex>\mathbb {O}=\omega </fr:tex>, we shall not have defined the “internal (pre)-<fr:tex>{\mathopen {}\left (\infty ,1\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>-topos of trees” in cubical assemblies.</fr:p><fr:p>More canonical approach would be to take internal presheaves on any <fr:tex>\mathcal {S}</fr:tex>-small well-founded order <fr:tex>\mathbb {O}</fr:tex> internal to the <fr:tex>{\mathopen {}\left (\infty ,1\right )\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>-category <fr:tex>\mathcal {E}</fr:tex> presented by <fr:tex>{\mathopen {}\left  [\square ^{\mathsf {op}},\mathbf {Asm}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathbb {A}\right )\mathclose {}}\right  ]\mathclose {}}</fr:tex>. This may introduce coherence problems that we are currently unprepared for.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter></fr:tree><fr:tree
